   {:e #blake3 "a51ac93de33f25af3e0e08c1a34c53790d2074e66123e5f9f1ad3499bbeae161" :a :task/description :v "BACKGROUND: compute_fitness() in bilateral.rs uses 7 hardcoded weight constants (W_VALIDATION=0.18..W_UNCERTAINTY=0.12) and 7 hardcoded component functions. Per INV-FOUNDATION-007, every aspect of the coherence model must derive from policy datoms. This task makes compute_fitness read boundary weights from the store, using BoundaryRegistry as the primary fitness computation path.. APPROACH: (1) Add fn load_policy_boundaries(store) -> Vec<(String, f64, Box<dyn BoundaryCheck>)> that queries :policy/boundary-* entities and constructs BoundaryCheck implementations dynamically. (2) For each boundary, the source/target patterns determine what entities to scan. Weight comes from :policy/boundary-weight. (3) Add fn compute_fitness_from_policy(store) -> FitnessScore that uses BoundaryRegistry populated from policy datoms. (4) In the main compute_fitness() path: if policy datoms exist, use compute_fitness_from_policy. If not, fall back to current hardcoded path (backward compatible). (5) MaterializedViews.fitness() must also read from policy when available — this means the policy weights are cached at store load time alongside the Views.. ACCEPTANCE: (A) compute_fitness_from_policy(store_with_ddis_manifest) matches old compute_fitness within epsilon 0.001. (B) compute_fitness_from_policy(store_with_no_policy) returns 1.0 (vacuously coherent). (C) compute_fitness_from_policy(store_with_custom_2_boundary_policy) correctly uses only 2 boundaries with custom weights. (D) BoundaryRegistry.total_coverage() is used as primary path. (E) Performance: policy datom query happens once at store load, not per fitness call. (F) Proptest: for random valid policies (1-10 boundaries, weights summing to 1.0), F(S) is always in [0,1]. DEPENDS-ON: POLICY-1 (t-f5298b23), POLICY-2 (t-5357604e). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs" :op :assert}
